INSERT INTO `spell` VALUES (1,'Aberto','','Charm',''),(2,'Accio','Summoning Charm','Charm','Summons an object towards the caster. It is able to summon objects in direct line of sight of the caster as well as things out of view by calling the object aloud after the incantation (unless the spell is casted nonverbally). This spell needs thought behind it and the object must be clear in the casters mind before trying to summon it. The caster doesnt necessarily need to know the location of the target if they say the name of the object to be summoned such as when Hermione Granger summoned some books from Dumbledores office simply by saying Accio Horcrux books! while in Gryffindor Tower.'),(3,'Age Line','','Charm','Prevents people above or below a certain age from access to a target.'),(4,'Aguamenti','Water-Making Spell','Charm Conjuration','Produces a clean drinkable jet of water from the wand tip.'),(5,'Alarte Ascendare','','Charm','Shoots the target high into the air.'),(6,'Albus Dumbledores forceful spell','','Spell','This spell was supposedly quite powerful as when it was cast the opponent was forced to conjure a silver shield to deflect it.'),(7,'Alohomora','Unlocking Charm','Charm','Unlocks doors and other objects. It can also unlock doors that have been sealed with a Locking Spell although it is possible to bewitch doors to become unaffected by this spell.'),(8,'Amato Animo Animato Animagus','Animagus Spell','Transfiguration','Spell used as part of the process of becoming an Animagus. The incantation has to be recited at sunrise and sundown every day before the consumption of the Animagus Potion. The incantation is also recited just prior to the consumption of the potion which has to take place just after a lightning storm starts. The incantation is recited while placing the wands tip over ones heart.'),(9,'Anapneo','','Healing Spell Vanishment','Clears the targets airway if they are choking on something.'),(10,'Anteoculatia','','Hex','Causes the target to grow antlers.'),(11,'Anti-Cheating Spell','','Charm','Used to prevent cheating.'),(12,'Anti-Disapparition Jinx','','Jinx','Prevents Disapparation in an area. It is used to entrap an enemy in an area.'),(13,'Anti-intruder jinx','','Jinx','Prevents intruders from entering an area.'),(14,'Antonin Dolohovs curse','','Curse','An unknown curse that causes injuries that are capable of killing with enough power.'),(15,'Aparecium','Revealing Charm','Charm','Reveals secret messages written in invisible ink or any other hidden markings. Also works against Concealing charms'),(16,'Appare Vestigium','Tracking Spell','Charm','Reveals traces of magic including footprints and track marks.'),(17,'Apparition','','Transportation','Magically transports the caster to another location instantaneously. The destination is one that the primary user has been to or seen in some fashion previously. Can be used to apparate multiple people at once if holding each other. No incantation required.'),(18,'Aqua Eructo','Aqua Eructo Charm','Charm','This spell is used to create and control a jet of clear water from the tip of the wand; it is probably related to Aguamenti.'),(19,'Arania Exumai','Spider repelling spell','Charm','Drives away spiders including Acromantulas.'),(20,'Arresto Momentum','Slowing Charm','Charm','Decreases the velocity of a moving target. Can be used on multiple targets as well as on the caster themselves. It was invented by Daisy Pennifold in 1711 for use on the Quaffle in Quidditch.'),(21,'Arrow-shooting spell','','Conjuration','Fires arrows from the casters wand.'),(22,'Ascendio','','Charm','Lifts the caster high into the air. The charm also works underwater propelling the caster above the surface.'),(23,'Avada Kedavra','Killing Curse','Curse',''),(24,'Avifors','Avifors Spell','Transfiguration','Transforms the target into a bird.'),(25,'Avenseguim','','Charm','Turns an object into a tracking device.'),(26,'Avis','Bird-Conjuring Charm','Conjuration Charm','Conjures a flock of birds from the tip of the wand. When used in conjunction with Oppugno it can be used offensively.'),(27,'Babbling Curse','','Curse','Causes uncontrollable babbling.'),(28,'Badgering','','Transfiguration','Turns things into badgers'),(29,'Bat-Bogey Hex','','Hex','Transforms the targets bogeys into large bats that fly out of the victims nose. It was invented by Miranda Goshawk.'),(30,'Baubillious','','Charm','The exact effects of the spell are unknown though it presumably is of damaging nature and it produces a bolt of white light from the tip of the wand.'),(31,'Bedazzling Hex','','Hex','Allows the caster to disguise things.'),(32,'Bewitched Snowballs','','Charm','Causes snowballs to pelt themselves at the target.'),(33,'Bluebell Flames','','Charm','Produces magical blue flames that can be held in a jar. Not as dangerous as real fire these magical flames can be touched penetrated and held without it burning the holder though it is known to singe materials such as clothing and plants.'),(34,'Blue sparks','','Charm','Jet of blue sparks. It can be used offensively as a minor duelling spell.'),(35,'Bombarda','Exploding Charm','Charm','Provokes a small explosion.'),(36,'Bombarda Maxima','','Charm','Creates a large explosion capable of removing entire walls. A more advanced and more powerful form of the Exploding Charm.'),(37,'Brackium Emendo','','Charm Healing Spell','If used correctly it is claimed that this spell will heal broken bones; this theory is supported by the etymology.'),(38,'Bravery Charm','','Charm','Increases the bravery of a teammate increasing their performance against certain foes.'),(39,'Bridge-conjuring spell','','Charm','Conjure a bridge from thin air.'),(40,'Broom jinx','','Jinx','Used to make broomsticks try to throw their riders off through a variety of means such as sudden lurches and violent swishing movements. Constant eye contact is needed for the jinx to keep working.'),(41,'Bubble-Head Charm','','Charm','Produces a large bubble of air around the head of the user; it is commonly used as the supernatural equivalent of a breathing set.'),(42,'Bubble-producing spell','','Charm','Produces a stream of non-bursting bubbles; there are two similar spells.'),(43,'Calvorio','Hair-Loss Curse','Curse','Removes the victims hair.'),(44,'Cantis','','Jinx','Causes the victim to burst uncontrollably into song.'),(45,'Capacious extremis','Extension Charm','Charm','Expands the internal dimensions of an object without affecting the external dimensions enhancing its capacity and rendering its contents lighter.'),(46,'Carpe Retractum','Seize and Pull Charm','Charm','Produces a rope of light used to pull objects towards the caster or if the target is fixed in place to pull the caster towards the target.'),(47,'Cascading Jinx','','Jinx','Attacks multiple opponents in close proximity to each other.'),(48,'Caterwauling Charm','','Charm','Anyone entering the perimeter of this spell sets off a high-pitched shriek. This spell may be related to the Intruder Charm.'),(49,'Cauldron to Sieve','','Transfiguration','Transforms cauldrons into sieves.'),(50,'Cauldron to badger','','Transfiguration','Transforms cauldrons into badgers.'),(51,'Cave inimicum','','Charm','Produces a boundary that keeps the caster hidden from others.'),(52,'Cheering Charm','','Charm','Makes the target feel happy. Overuse of the spell may cause the target to break into an uncontrollable laughing fit. This spell was invented by Felix Summerbee.'),(53,'Circumrota','','Charm','Rotates objects.'),(54,'Cistem Aperio','','Charm','Opens chests and boxes.'),(55,'Colloportus','Locking Spell','Charm','Locks doors and all things that can be locked. It is the counter-charm to the Unlocking Spell.'),(56,'Colloshoo','Stickfast Hex','Hex','Sticks the targets shoes to the ground.'),(57,'Colovaria','Colour Change Charm','Charm','Changes the targets colour.'),(58,'Confringo','Blasting Curse','Curse','Produces a fiery explosion.'),(59,'Confundo','Confundus Charm','Charm','Causes the victim to become confused and befuddled.'),(60,'Conjunctivitis Curse','','Curse','Causes irritation in the eyes forcing them to swell shut. The Oculus Potion is able to counteract this curse. Dragons are particularly susceptible to this curse as their hide makes them resistant to most spells while their eyes remain vulnerable.'),(61,'Cornflake skin spell','',NULL,'This spell causes the victims skin to appear as though it was coated in cornflakes.'),(62,'Cracker Jinx','','Jinx','This spell is used to conjure exploding wizard crackers; it can be used in duelling to harm the opponent but the force of the explosion may also affect the caster.'),(63,'Cribbing Spell','','Spell','This spell which may possibly be a charm is used to assist the caster in cheating on written papers tests and exams. It is possible that these spells can negate anti-cheating spells.'),(64,'Crinus Muto','','Transfiguration','Used to transfigure the colour and style of ones hair.'),(65,'Crucio','Cruciatus Curse','Curse','Inflicts intense pain on the recipient of the curse. This curse does not physically harm the victim but may in extreme cases drive them insane. The pain is described as having hot knives being driven into the victim. It cannot be cast successfully by a person who is doing so out of pure spite or anger; one must feel a true desire to cause the victim pain. If one casts this spell he or she will receive a life sentence in Azkaban prison for it as with the other twoUnforgivable Curses.'),(66,'Defodio','Gouging Spell','Charm','Allows the caster to dig and carve through the target.'),(67,'Deletrius','Eradication Spell','Charm','Counter-charm to the Reverse Spell vanishing the image of the last spell cast. It may also disintegrate other certain images.'),(68,'Densaugeo','','Hex','This hex causes the victims teeth to grow rapidly but can also be used to restore lost teeth as proven when Ted Tonks did so in 1997 for Harry Potter.'),(69,'Deprimo','','Charm','Charm used to blast holes in the ground.'),(70,'Depulso','Banishing Charm','Charm','Sends the target away from the caster. It is the counter-charm to the Summoning Charm.'),(71,'Descendo','','Charm','Causes object to fall or move downwards.'),(72,'Desk Into Pig','','Transfiguration','Turns desks into pigs.'),(73,'Deterioration Hex','','Hex','Impairs foes and reduces their stamina.'),(74,'Diffindo','Severing Charm','Charm','Used to precisely cut or tear objects.'),(75,'Diminuendo','','Charm','Forces the target to shrink.'),(76,'Dissendium','','Charm','Used to open passages.'),(77,'Disillusionment Charm','','Charm','Causes the target to blend seamlessly in with its surroundings like a chameleon.'),(78,'Draconifors','Draconifors Spell','Transfiguration','Transforms the target into a dragon.'),(79,'Drought Charm','','Charm','Causes puddles and ponds to dry up. Though not powerful enough to drain a body of water like a lake'),(80,'Ducklifors','Ducklifors Jinx','Transfiguration Jinx','Transforms the target into a duck.'),(81,'Duro','Hardening Charm','Charm','Turns an object to stone.'),(82,'Ears to kumquats','','Transfiguration','This spell transforms the victims ears into kumquats.'),(83,'Ear-shrivelling Curse','','Curse','Causes the targets ears to shrivel up.'),(84,'Ebublio','Ebublio Jinx','Jinx','Causes the victim to inflate and explode into hundreds of bubbles; it can only be cast if an ally is using Aqua Eructo on the victim simultaneously.'),(85,'Engorgio','Engorgement Charm','Charm','Causes the target to swell in physical size. Its counter-charm is the Shrinking Charm.'),(86,'Engorgio Skullus','','Hex','Causes the victims skull to swell disproportionately. This spell may be a variation of the Engorgement Charm as they share the first word of the incantation. Its countercurse is Redactum Skullus.'),(87,'Entomorphis','Insect Jinx','Jinx Transfiguration','This hex is used to transform the target into an insectoid for a short time.'),(88,'Entrail-Expelling Curse','','Curse','Expels victims entrails. Precise effects unknown. Invented by Urquhart Rackharrow.'),(89,'Episkey','','Healing Spell','Used to heal relatively minor injuries such as broken bones and cartilage.'),(90,'Epoximise','','Transfiguration','Adheres one object to another as if they had been glued together.'),(91,'Erecto','','Charm','Used to erect a tent or other upright structure.'),(92,'Evanesce','','Transfiguration','Vanishes the target'),(93,'Evanesco','Vanishing Spell','Transfiguration','Vanishes the target. Vanished things go into non-being which is to say everything.'),(94,'Everte Statum','','Spell','Throws the victim backward similarly to being thrown.'),(95,'Expecto Patronum','Patronus Charm','Charm','This charm is a highly powerful and advanced protective spell which will conjure a spirit guardian of their positive emotions to defend against dark creatures; it can also send messages to other witches or wizards. The Patronus takes the form of an animal unique to each person who casts it. The form of a Patronus can change when one has undergone a period of heightened emotion.'),(96,'Expelliarmus','Disarming Charm','Charm','Forces whatever an opponent is holding to fly out of their hand. It was considered to be Harry Potters signature spell.'),(97,'Expulso','Expulso Curse','Curse','Provokes an explosion unique in that it uses pressure to do so as opposed to heat.'),(98,'Extinguishing Spell','','Charm','Puts out fires.'),(99,'False memory charm','','Charm','Implants a false memory in the victim without them realising it was not originally theirs.'),(100,'Feather-light charm','','Charm','Makes an object light as a feather.'),(101,'Ferret to human','','Transfiguration','Transforms a ferret into a human.'),(102,'Ferula','Bandaging Charm','Conjuration Healing spell','Conjures up bandages and wraps them around a wound splinting any broken bones.'),(103,'Fianto Duri','','Charm','A defensive charm which based on the etymology strengthens shield spells and perhaps objects in general in a similar way to Duro.'),(104,'Fidelius Charm','','Charm','An immensely complex charm used to hide secret information within the soul of the charms recipient who is called a Secret-Keeper. The information is irretrievable unless the Secret-Keeper willingly chooses to reveal it and only the aforementioned person can do so.'),(105,'Fiendfyre','','Curse','Unleashes cursed fire that takes the shape of animals that actively seek out living targets and burn anything in its path including nearly indestructable substances such as horcruxes. In addition this fire is made even more dangerous due to the fact that it is extremely difficult to control and cannot be extinguished with normal or enchanted water.'),(106,'Finestra','Finestra spell','Charm','Shatters glass.'),(107,'Finite Incantatem','General Counter-Spell','Counter-Spell','Terminates all spell effects in the vicinity of the caster.'),(108,'Finger-removing jinx','','Jinx','Removes a persons fingers.'),(109,'Firestorm','','Charm','Produces a ring of fire from the wand.'),(110,'Flagrante Curse','','Curse','Causes objects to burn on contact.'),(111,'Flagrate','','Charm','Writes in midair with firey marks.'),(112,'Flame-Freezing Charm','','Charm','Causes fire to tickle those caught in it instead of burning them.'),(113,'Flask-conjuring spell','','Conjuration','Conjures a glass flask'),(114,'Flintifors','','Transfiguration','Transforms objects into matchboxes.'),(115,'Flipendo','Knockback Jinx','Jinx','Knocks objects and creatures backwards.'),(116,'Flipendo Duo','Knockback Jinx Duo','Jinx','A more powerful version of Flipendo.'),(117,'Flipendo Tria','','Jinx','A more powerful version of Flipendo Duo; it is said to resemble a miniature tornado.'),(118,'Flying Charm','','Charm','This spell is cast on broomsticks and flying carpets to allow them to fly.'),(119,'Fumos','Smokescreen Spell','Charm','Defensive smokescreen that hinders visibility.'),(120,'Fumos Duo','','Charm','A more powerful version of Fumos.'),(121,'Furnunculus','Pimple Jinx','Jinx